title: Six stabbed at Yolo County party
text:
Six stabbed at Yolo County party 
18-year-old arrested apparently was not a guest 
Motive for quinceañera attack under investigation 
Covering crime, police and courts in the Sacramento region The incident occurred about 10:30 p.m. in the Madison Town Hall. googlemaps.com i 
Six people were stabbed at a quinceañera party in the Yolo County town of Madison on Saturday night, law officials said. 
An 18-year-old suspect, who apparently crashed the party, was arrested nearby just after the incident, Sgt. Don Harmon of the Yolo County Sheriff’s Office said. 
The incident occurred about 10:30 p.m. in the Madison Town Hall. All of the victims were adults, Harmon said. The stab wounds ranged from minor to serious. All were treated at a nearby hospital. One victim underwent surgery. 
Harmon said the motive for the attack is under investigation.  ;
